mpics are aquatics, athletics, canoeing, gymnastics, sport climbing, surfing, and wrestling.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Qualifying is ongoing among a number of different sports, and even those who arelisted belowmay change in terms of additions.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The standout names from those announced by SASCOC in Johannesburg on Wednesday included the double medalist from Tokyo 2020, swimmer Tatjana Smith (formerly Schoenmaker), swimmer Chad Le Clos, and sprinter Akani Simbine.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3955555355763414e-32, \"text\": \"Johannesburg\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\"}, {\"begin\": 776, \"end\": 781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7469365160493612, \"rank\": 0.33880186400892115, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 842, \"end\": 854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad Le Clos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\"}, {\"begin\": 869, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith won gold in the women's 200m breaststroke and silver in the 100m breaststroke in Tokyo, while Le Clos will be attending his fourth Olympics.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7469365160493612, \"rank\": 0.33880186400892115, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joins an exclusive club including Khotso Mokoena, Ryk Neethling, Hendrik Ramaala, Roland Schoeman, and Sunette Viljoen.\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1085, \"end\": 1098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryk_Neethling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryk Neethling\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryk_Neethling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryk_Neethling\"}, {\"begin\": 1100, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hendrick_Ramaala\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hendrik Ramaala\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hendrick_Ramaala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hendrick_Ramaala\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roland_Schoeman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roland Schoeman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roland_Schoeman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roland_Schoeman\"}, {\"begin\": 1138, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunette_Viljoen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunette Viljoen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunette_Viljoen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunette_Viljoen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Le Clos has already entered the history books as the winner of the most Olympic medals (four) by a South African and he will be looking to add to that tally in Paris.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2281406429824858e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another medalist who will be at the Olympics in Paris is the men's 400m gold hero from Rio 2016, Wayde van Niekerk.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2281406429824858e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1410, \"end\": 1413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.413854941685476e-33, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His 43.03 seconds on that occasion remains the world record.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women'sathletics representativesinclude three in the marathon - Gerda Steyn, 15th in Tokyo 2020, who has since lowered the South African record to 2hr 24min 3sec and is widely considered the world's finest ultra-marathoner.\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1569, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\", \"score\": 0.9999998978501078, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerda Steyn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\"}, {\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7469365160493612, \"rank\": 0.33880186400892115, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cian Oldknow, and Irvette van Zyl, who is attending her third Olympics.\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1729, \"end\": 1733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\", \"score\": 0.999999978574124, \"rank\": 2.1331004943414493e-08, \"text\": \"Cian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\"}, {\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irvette van Zyl\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One gold medalist from the recent African Games in Ghana has also been included in the initial squad and will be making her first Olympic appearance - women's 400m hurdles athlete Rogain Joseph.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1853, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re